The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 October is 80,637 (9,293.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 October, there were 2,401 new confirmed cases (276.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 September, there were 2,511 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (110 fewer cases).
